HEADWORD: Purgament
<hw>Pur"ga*ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>purgamentum</ets> offscourings, washings, expiatory sacrifice. See
<er>Purge</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>That which is excreted;
excretion.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A cathartic; a purgative.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Purgation</ent>⟦br⟧
